ttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book explores the interfaces of English as a Lingua Franca (ELF) and English as a Foreign Language (EFL) pedagogy. It presents the theoretical aspects of ELF, discusses issues and challenges that ELF raises for the EFL classroom, and demonstrates how EFL practitioners can make use of ELF theorizing for classroom instruction, teacher education, developing language learning materials, policymaking and testing and assessment. Accounts of innovative and practical pedagogical practices and researchers’ insights from diverse geographical, cultural and institutional contexts will inform and inspire EFL practitioners to reconsider their practices and adopt new techniques in order to meet their learners’ diverse communicative needs in international contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexGlobalization. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aEnglish languagezForeign countries. 0aLingua francas. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / English as a Second Language.2bisacsh  aAssessment and testing.  aEFL.  aEnglish as a Foreign Language.  aEnglish as a Lingua Franca.  aEnglish language pedagogy.  aEnglish teaching methods.  aLanguage teaching materials.  aTeacher education .  aWorld Englishes.1 aBayyurt, Yasemin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCavalheiro, Lili, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFay, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuerra, Luís, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemaloglu-Er, Elif, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirkpatrick, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relator